SHINLAE OCEANWALKER
</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzandorfz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zandorfz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/28/02 8:10:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> I am learning more and more that timing helps a lot.  I.e. casting stun just after seeing the &quot;npc begins to cast&quot; message works great - *if* you don't have a laggy connection.  With a lot of lag, I sometimes just continuously rotate the stuns, but this uses more mana and is less effective.  A simple clarity I pretty much keeps my mana up when doing this, however.<br>
<br>
I have just started to group in Seb, and I can sometimes keep the caster frogs from getting off more than a couple spells a fight.  The difference between doing this or not is reflected in the health-bars of the group (or the amount of mana burned by the cleric).  The amount Paladins contribute to the health and efficiency of a group in this fashion is quite impressive, IMHO.<br>
<br>
Zandorf<br>
54 Paladin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaldolurbritebeard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldolur Britebeard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/28/02 9:43:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> Thank you, noble Deezle! That helps tremendously... I'm anxious to set it all up and start working with it! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><TABLE><TR><TD style="filter:glow(color=00AA00 strength=2); font-family:Times Roman; font-weight:bold; font-size:8pt"><I><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124984" target="new"><FONT size=2 color=#FFFF33>Sir Kaldolur Britebeard</FONT></A></I><BR><FONT face="Verdana" color="#FFFFFF">49th Paladin of Brell
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<font size="2" face="verdana"> 
<BR><i>"SHORT BEER?! What is that, some kind of joke?!"</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaldolurbritebeard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldolur Britebeard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/2/02 5:17:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> Just a quick follow up... Been using the above tactic(s) over the past several days. It's a whole new world - hehe... Thank you once again, everyone who offered their advice. You just increased my usefulness to my group ten-fold. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><TABLE><TR><TD style="filter:glow(color=00AA00 strength=2); font-family:Times Roman; font-weight:bold; font-size:8pt"><I><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124984" target="new"><FONT size=2 color=#FFFF33>Sir Kaldolur Britebeard</FONT></A></I><BR><FONT face="Verdana" color="#FFFFFF">49th Paladin of Brell
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<font size="2" face="verdana"> 
<BR><i>"SHORT BEER?! What is that, some kind of joke?!"</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uboleslav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boleslav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/2/02 6:30:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> I use the stuns as described above, but do not use a 1HS/Shield combo.  I find I can still shut down casting mobs very efficiently.  I use Cease, Stun, and Holy Might as my stuns.  I also find that I can shut down most blue mobs for about 2/3 of a fight chain casting Stun and Holy Might.  If I have a clarity, and am not pulling I can do this fairly continuously.  This reduces the amount of damage the mobs do considerably.  It also increases the number of hunting options available to whatever group I am in.<br>
<br>
Cracked myself up the other day.  I was in a group with an enchanter and two 60th level warriors in Akheva Ruins.  As a lark, we decided that I would tank so they could focus on damage instead of aggro control.  I was able to keep aggro over 80% of the time, and still keep most of the mobs from hitting well over half the time from stuns.  We didn't have a cleric, but were still able to keep an impressive kill rate going because we weren't taking much damage.  The chanter was 60, so I had KEI, and the mobs were slowed and tashed, which helped a lot.  It was a lot of fun trying to out taunt 2 warriors 6 levels higher than me though.  Anyway, stuns are a BIG part of our arsenal.<br>
<br>
Boleslav Forgehammer<br>
Paladin of Brell in his 54th Campaign<br>
E'ci<br>
Blacksmithing - 250<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvarutiasilvon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varutia Silvon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/3/02 2:11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> Stun is one of the most important spell you will use. I mem three of them. I also use stun to ghetto slow mobs, or sometimes when they hit too fast you find hard to get a spell off, just chuck a holy might and follow up with the spell you need to cast.<br>
<br>
I had evocation at 9 at level 27, then I went to unrest and got the skill up to 100 or so. Then with the level 30 stun, mine evocation is maxed at every level very quickly. (Don't have cesist, desist, back then and didn't find much use for that undead dd, til I got to unrest)<br>
<br>
Keep practicing it, as you WILL have use for it. Also new spells tend to fizzle more, as you level up, even with the same skill level, you will fizzle less.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177561>Varutia Silvonesit </a><BR>Level 57 Knight<BR>Trailblazers of Norrath<BR>Terris Thule</center><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uspiritbladetherathe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spiritblade TheRathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/3/02 4:17:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> Chain Stun = mad agro, if you want to tank also <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Mobs really dont like your stunning them, and i keep 2-3 stuns mem'ed at all times. <br>
<br>
Spiritblade<br>
Lvl 60 Crusader<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171331">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=171331</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usoraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soraden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/9/02 3:13:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15920.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Difficulties...</span><hr size=1> Cease and Desist are interrupt spells.  So the mob isn't actually &quot;stunned&quot;.  It's pretty much like bash.<br>
Stun, Holy Might, Force, Words of Tranquility are your stuns.  Those will actually stop the mob from doing anything for a few seconds.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is that you load up cease, desist and stun.  Get a Clarity or C2(C3 if you're lucky) and chain stun a moss snake or something hehe.  Or chain stun someone's pet.  (not sure if NPC's will agro you if you cast on a pet)  <br>
<br>
You definately wanna max your evocation, alteration and abjuration.  (Divination too.. so you don't fizzle on IVU at the wrong time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p><font size = 1 color=white><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168892>Baron Dvarian, 60th Warder of Povar</b></font>
<br>
<font size = 1 color=white> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168878>Baron Soraden, 57th Knight</a></font>
<br>
<font size = 1 color=white><b>Tvarian 55th Preserver</b></font>
<BR>
